{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"body":"Plan-review PASS (signed) on iteration 3 after 2 remediations: (1) reframed to metadata-only classifier respecting the multi-seam reality; (2) dropped the dangling typed-error-subclass deliverable + made every mapping row a concrete matchable artifact. Implemented + committed ed47d9289. Advisory triage (15 advisories, all addressed in CODE to preserve the signed attestation rather than re-editing the description): E6/F1 err.outcome -> added runner-wiring test; E1/T8 exc-required -> made exc default None (finish_reason-only classification); G6/G1G2 context-length -> local hint list documented as mirroring sizing.is_context_limit_error + preservation test; T3 ordering -> ModelHTTPError matched before ModelAPIError (comment+covered); E2/T8 hex/base64 thresholds -> impl uses {32,}/{40,}; T8 diagnostic keys -> _ALLOWED_FIELDS canonical set; T8 placeholder -> {exception_type,message:'diagnostic unavailable'}. JUSTIFIED-not-fixed: T1 lint.py redactor reuse — kept failure.py's redactor self-contained; the two serve different surfaces (workflow-YAML secret-scan-for-display vs LLM-diagnostic inline-scrub) and coupling the low-level classifier boundary (drake imports it) to workflow/lint.py would be a worse dependency. T1 httpx-not-declared — httpx is guaranteed present transitively (pydantic-ai-slim/anthropic) wherever this agents-gated module is reachable. 38 new tests green; arawana matrix + 71 runner/structured tests green; mypy clean. Not closing until Verified +1."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1783647586292190001,"uuid":"e9866d29-78ec-439c-b2e7-eddbe5ad8f30"}